while luna certainly ca n't be accused of creating happy pop music the jaunty dear diary comes close there is a sly smile and wink inherent in the songs of dean wareham 's new york moody atmospheric quartet the textured often psychedelic guitar work mixed with wry lyricism demand comparisons with the velvet underground and at their most hypnotic and somnambulistic they even conjure up the warm comforting sounds of early rem retaining his world weary vocals from his former band galaxie 500 mr wareham is the glue that holds this ethereal sounding band together the test they sing in german without seeming pretentious and they perform a guns n roses classic sweet child o mine turning it into a graceful moodpiece luna appears at 10 pm friday and next saturday at maxwell 's 1039 washington street hoboken 201 653 1703 robbie woliver

